reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I often see people looking at the K version of this chip as a better option. I would argue against that philosophy. Having had the 9900k for the past few years, I struggled with going down to a locked i7. I could not be happier with my decision. I have used the cpu in both capped and uncapped throttling. I have settled on capped which runs at 5.2ghz across 8 cores and my cpu never gets above 50 degrees celsius on high end settings of games running with other apps open. The absolute positive for me is that I dropped from an AIO pump to a blade fin standard cooler. As a result the computer is cooler and fans run slower making the room less noisy and less heat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Used and surprisingly good
reviews.reviewText: Having been burned by "like-new" electronics riddled with missing parts and broken pins, I was pleasantly surprised by this impeccable microprocessor. From its meticulous cleaning and repackaging to the prompt shipping and flawless performance, it's evident that Techno Intelligence (the company shipping it) takes pride in exceeding expectations. Highly recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars One of the best CPUs you can buy for gaming and content creation
reviews.reviewText: The Intel Core i7-13700 is a beast of a processor. It's packed with features that make it a great choice for gamers, creative professionals, and anyone who wants the best possible performance.The i7-13700 has 12 cores and 20 threads and it's also clocked at 5.1 GHz, which is one of the highest clock speeds of any mainstream processor.In terms of performance, the i7-13700 is simply outstanding. It's the second fastest processor that Intel has ever released, and it's even faster than all of AMD's CPUs except the 7950x. In benchmarks, the i7-13700 consistently outperforms its predecessor, the i7-12700K, by a significant margin.Overall, the Intel Core i7-13700 is an excellent processor. It's the second best that Intel has to offer, and it's a great choice for anyone who wants the best possible performance.Here are some of the pros and cons of the Intel i7-13700:Pros: 12 cores for cheap Blazing fast performance Excellent multi-tasking capabilities Best for gaming New Raptor Lake architecture Up to 5.1 GHz clock speedCons: Not overclockableIf you're looking for a new processor, the i7-13700 is definitely one of the best CPUs you can buy

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice CPU- 13th gen Intel with low 65W TDP
reviews.reviewText: This is a GREAT little CPU. Super fasssssst with very low 65W TDP. Multiple cores handle video game processing with ease. Includes onboard video (if needed). Get yourself a good air cooler ( Thermalrite Assassin) and check your mobo CPU Turbo settings for PL1 and PL2. Start with 65W and 219W settings (per Intel). Even today, this CPU is commanding a bit of a premium price but it is still cheaper than the 13700K or KF versions. This is kind of a sleeper in the 13th gen series. Buy it !
